# Architecture Overview

## Folder Layout

```
src/
  features/<feature>/
    pages/       # route-level screen composition only
    hooks/       # orchestration: state, async, actions
    domain/      # pure business logic, no React/side-effects
    data/        # API calls, repositories, DTO mapping
    components/  # presentational, feature-specific
  components/
    ui/          # shadcn/radix primitives
    shared/      # reusable app-level widgets (2+ features)
  config/
    routes.ts    # route path source-of-truth
  libs/           # framework-agnostic utilities
  types/         # shared domain contracts
  utils/         # app-specific runtime helpers
```

## Dependency Direction (strict)

```
pages → hooks → domain / data
component → props ← page/hook
shared → no feature-specific imports
```

## Layer Contracts

| Layer | Allowed | Forbidden |
|---|---|---|
| `domain` | pure TS, no imports from other layers | React, side effects, API calls |
| `data` | API/fetch, DTO mapping | UI components, React hooks |
| `hooks` | state, async, React hooks, domain/data | direct API calls bypassing data layer |
| `pages` | layout, routing, wiring hook+component | business logic, direct repo calls |
| `components` | props-driven UI | direct API calls, global state mutation |

## Cross-Feature Rule

- Import across features only via `features/<name>/index.ts`
- Never import `@/features/x/data/*` or `@/features/x/domain/*` directly
- Shared logic used in 2+ features → move to `lib`, `types`, or `components/shared`

## Route Convention

- All paths declared in `src/config/routes.ts`
- Never hardcode path strings (e.g. `"/tenants/123"`) — use `routePathBuilders.*`
- New route: add to `routes.ts` → register in `app-routes.tsx` → update nav if needed
